<item>
            <title>[LU-15179] sanity-quota tests don&apos;t cleanup space causing later tests to fail</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15179</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Tests&#160;39, 40a, 40b, 40c, 40d, 50, 51, 52, 53, 55, 56, 57, 59, 62, 64, 65, 76 use setup_quota_test without &quot;stack_trap cleanup_quota_test&quot;. For example, if sanity-quota_55 fails it does not cleanup quota space causing to fail later tests: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing-archive.whamcloud.com/gerrit-janitor/18638/testresults/sanity-quota-ldiskfs-DNE-centos7_x86_64-centos7_x86_64/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing-archive.whamcloud.com/gerrit-janitor/18638/testresults/sanity-quota-ldiskfs-DNE-centos7_x86_64-centos7_x86_64/.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another problem is that sanity-quota_75 doesn&apos;t remove tdir_dom. This also makes impossible to land new quota patches with tests.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
